README:

Adriatic Coast
<hr>
Counter Strike Source (CSS) Bomb Defusion Map (de_adriatic)
<hr>
AUTHOR: Simon 'Hurtz' Davies

E-MAIL: mjrhurtz@spl33n.co.uk

FILENAME: de_adriatic.bsp

DESCRIPTION: A small coastal town is disrupted by a terrorist attack to destroy commercial operations in the area.

In game description...

Counter-Terrorists:
Prevent Terrorist operatives from disrupting commercial operations at this coastal industrial town. Two viable targets, cargo crates currently located on a nearby roof top, or the computer terminals in the dock building.
Terrorists:
Disrupt commercial operations by the destruction of vital cargo crates or computer systems in the dock building, controlling shipping in the local area.

Details: 32 Players max. 16 Player starts each side.

COMMENTS: 

This is my first real foray into level creation for a source title other than a few test maps for Half-Life 2 Deathmatch, and I am fairly happy with it.

Bot support included in the .bsp file. Bots do not take every path, although this is barely noticeable (dont go over crates by the wall for example.) Sometimes get stuck on the doors, otherwise fairly good.

Optimisation isnt great, but overall is fairly smooth with only some areas with noticeable slow down. (on my system at least.)

Map de_adriatic copyright(c) Hurtz 2007, feel free to distribute as long as the file(s) remains unchanged.

Thanks to the Incredible: Chizbone  for tuning my nav mesh
(he is also the nav_editor of cs_atafaris+ ,de_phoenix_steel and de_cityfever)


For both teams are two spawn/startpoints added to make the game more interesting and not repeating itself round for round for round.
So its more tactic and random start-standups for each team.


Please note, that you can support your team from both bombspots while planting/defusing the bomb!!!

There are several ways between the bombspots to increase the gameflow, underground and overground (at the rooftops) + you have an advantage while shooting from the roof!

This map was originally created for the 2008 Joe.To Abstract Mappack, which can be found here: http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/58046

Depending on your graphics settings, certain things in this map may or may not appear as was intended. So be sure to keep that in mind. Certain things, like the art gallery bombsite for example, will NOT look right on DX level 8.1 or lower.

In this map, there are secrets, traps, absurdity and other assorted crazyness. So be on your guard!

As usual, special thanks go out to the joe.to community, and all who gave me very useful tips and criticism to help make this map better. You guys should have seen my original version. I mean, the FIRST, FIRST one before I deleted entire rooms and started over. Horrible.

Enjoy!

Very esthetically pleasing; this is one of those maps that truly has a theme to it. Though the map is made to resemble a historical mountain mansion or an abby of some sort (most likely the latter, hence the name), you do get the sense that it is inhabited. From the breathtaking central area to the waterfall to the little cross on the distant mountain, de_abbaye is truly beautiful. However, if I'm not mistaken, I do seem to be missing one texture (a painting or something on a few walls, noticeably in the indoor CT spawn area with the computers), and the waterfall sound could be a bit louder. Other than that, the map is relatively complex, with many hallways and exits, and definitely fun to explore. Awesome Job.

Map description                        
==================
This map is **complete**. It contains ambient and door sounds, highly customized bot navigation, radar, HDR lighting, area names, cubemaps and dynamic NPC and prop shadows. This map has been updated and is now designed for **32 PLAYERS**.

**BombsiteA** contains highly-valuable crates of nuclear weapons which are to be delivered to the US military base tonight

**BombsiteB** contains remenants of radioactive waste, however this is located above the cities main sewerage system. If the radioactive waste is leaked into the system, the coastline will become contaminated

_Designer Note: The map encourages the use of smoke grenades and flanking_

Your thoughts on the map? chuck them below. _Rate, comment and enjoy!_ cheers and have a good day.
